node.text: These are the tough conversations we need to have. Even if you don’t think you are racist, it’s imperative that we all educate ourselves to understand the magnitude of systemic racism. I am engaged to an amazing human being who also happens to be black. And while I love him more than anything and have learned a lot about his experience, I still must continue to educate myself because I can never walk in his shoes. I/WE must understand history in order to understand the present and make changes for the future. Thank you @themanacho for creating this video and teaching people who don’t understand completely how they can continue to learn and grow. This is just the beginning, we have a lot of work to do. ✊🏿✊🏾✊🏽✊🏼✊🏻 #leadbyexample #bethechange

node.text: Today reminds me of all the incredible memories I have from the Olympics. Walking in the opening and closing ceremonies representing your country… its an experience I’ll never forget.  As the summer Olympics begin today, I believe it comes at an important time for the world; giving all of us the hope and inspiration we need. For me personally, I am continuously inspired by these athletes and I cannot wait to watch them. Good luck to my fellow Americans and all athletes and officials. 🙏🏻💪🏻❤️🇺🇸 #olympics #toyko
